set_seed
    set the random seed to the cpu
    
SYNOPSIS   
    subroutine set_seed(idum)
    
    integer idum
PURPOSE
	set the random seed to the cpu. idum is the seed. If idum=0, then the seed will generate by cpu

PARAMETERS
	idum      - integer -
	          idum=0, then the random seed will be set by cpu
	          if idum not equal to 0, it will be the random seed

EXAMPLT


   integer::seed
   seed=-1
   call set_seed(seed)
